Terraform is an open-source Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tool developed by HashiCorp.
It allows you to define, provision, and manage infrastructure across multiple cloud providers â€” such as AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud â€” using a simple and declarative configuration language.

ğŸ§  What is Terraform?
Terraform is a tool for Building,Changing,Versioning infrastructure safely and Efficiently.
Instead of manually setting up servers, networks, and storage through cloud consoles, Terraform lets you write configurations in .tf files â€” which describe what you want your infrastructure to look like.

Terraform then takes care of:

Creating resources

Updating configurations

Destroying unused resources
